==================================================
CHANGE — Hexagonal architecture setup
Date: 2026-03-30
==================================================

==================================================
GOAL
==================================================

Introduce a first-pass hexagonal architecture without changing the external API.

This setup is intended to:

1. move HTTP and worker wiring off direct storage access
2. define explicit outbound ports for repositories, queue publishing, and code execution
3. keep the domain/application logic testable without Gin, GORM, Redis, or Docker

==================================================
WHAT CHANGED
==================================================

1. PORTS

  Added:
    internal/port/

  Defines outbound interfaces for:
    - problems
    - submissions
    - sessions
    - reviews
    - registry
    - test cases
    - evaluation publisher
    - code runner

2. ADAPTERS

  Added:
    internal/adapter/storage/
    internal/adapter/queue/
    internal/adapter/sandbox/

  Current adapters:
    - storage adapters wrap internal/storage GORM stores
    - queue adapter wraps asynq publishing
    - sandbox adapter wraps sandbox.Run

3. APPLICATION LAYER

  Added:
    internal/application/api.go
    internal/application/evaluation.go

  Current app services:
    - APIService
      handles problem lookup/list/suggest, submissions, progress, timers,
      reviews, and registry sync/version reads
    - EvaluationService
      handles judge-worker evaluation flow through ports

4. WIRING

  Updated:
    cmd/api-server/handler/*
    cmd/judge-worker/evaluator.go

  Result:
    - handlers now call application services
    - worker now calls EvaluationService
    - direct handler-to-storage coupling was removed from the main API path

5. TESTS

  Added:
    internal/application/api_test.go

  Current unit coverage:
    - submission creation publishes evaluation job
    - publisher errors bubble up
    - problem lookup falls back to slug path

==================================================
CURRENT STATE
==================================================

- storage remains a GORM + goose adapter layer
- api-server now depends on application services + ports
- judge-worker now depends on EvaluationService + ports
- local-agent has not been hexagonalized yet
- domain package remains the center and is still infra-free

==================================================
NEXT RECOMMENDED STEP
==================================================

1. move local-agent logic behind ports/use-cases too
2. add more unit tests for timer/progress/evaluation application services
3. document the new package dependency rules in docs/architecture.md
